cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DC

The paper discusses the missing links in the BGP-based AS connectivity maps, which is related to network measurements and network topology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses security issues related to BGP, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions the use of information theory to analyze the connectivity maps, which is related to cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of missing links on network performance, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
